author: COMSOL
description: This example investigates the electrical and thermal characteristics of a plasma DC arc created in a point-to-plane configuration. The discharge is assumed to be in local thermodynamic equilibrium. The plasma is considered a conductive fluid medium and is modeled using a magnetohydrodynamics approach. This model shows how to use the Magnetohydrodynamics, Out-of-Plane Currents interface to simulate the plasma generated in a DC arc.
